{"name":"Wilderness Survival","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 41\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Hunting, trapping, fishing, boating, shelter building, fire building (including tribal smoke signals), logging, woodworking, raft building, and so on. These tasks are performed without need of a check; they are simply the huntsman&rsquo;s province. Under adverse conditions, the referee may assign a reasonable probability of success. Whether a chance of failure applies is at the discretion of the referee, as reflected by the prevailing conditions and abilities of the huntsman.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"huntsman","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.T8VdjzWDNBWfyZ8S"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679252841676,"modifiedTime":1681579182867,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"0hBRKgufAV98GAv2","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Climb","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 37\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 39\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To ascend or descend sheer cliffs or walls without need of climbing gear, if lightly armoured or unarmoured, as a thief of equal level (see <strong>Table 16</strong>). Chance-in- twelve reduced by 4 if wearing medium <span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">armour; impossible in heavy armour. If vertical, the surface must be rough or cracked. At least one check must be made per 100 feet of climbing. Failure indicates the climber has slipped and fallen at about the midpoint of the check.</span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>[<strong>Table 16: Progressive Thief Abilities</strong> -- see <strong>Player's Manual</strong>, p.37]</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"huntsman","roll":"d12","rollType":"below","rollTarget":8,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679253059188,"modifiedTime":1681579182865,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"7ChvOS1KtyNKjtbN","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Werewolf Slayer","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 50\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>At 4th level, huntsmen develop the aptitude to slay lycanthropes. Indeed, when men and women suffer the curse of the beast, huntsmen rise to stamp them out. When wielding silver or magical weapons versus lycanthropes, huntsmen gain all the benefits of the <em>predator</em> ability, regardless of the advanced intelligence of the afflicted.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"huntsman","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.T8VdjzWDNBWfyZ8S"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679252841676,"modifiedTime":1681579182866,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"F6muUNBMrw6clv7V","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Ambusher","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 39\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>When traversing the wilds alone or with others of like ability, the huntsman&rsquo;s base <em>surprize</em> chance increases by one (+1) on a d6 roll. Furthermore, when outdoors, even an untrained party&rsquo;s chance to surprize increases by one (+1) if the huntsman positions and prepares them accordingly.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"huntsman","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679254261847,"modifiedTime":1681579182865,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"NoxyIedR71kcOuQa","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Subdue Animal","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 49\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To soothe and tame an animal (normal, not magical) of hit dice equal to or less than the huntsman&rsquo;s level. To succeed, the following steps must be completed:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Through combat, physically reduce the animal to half or less its hit point total (the huntsman can assess this with accuracy). The huntsman must be a prominent aggressor in the beast&rsquo;s impairment.</li>\n<li>Restrain the creature. Many a huntsman will use a bola, lasso, fighting net, or whip to make <em>prone</em> the target before attempting to restrain it.</li>\n<li>On the round following restraint, the huntsman attempts to assert mental and physical dominance. The base chance of success is 4-in-12. This chance-in-twelve may be increased by the following modifiers:\n<ul>\n<li>+1 if the huntsman&rsquo;s strength is 16+</li>\n<li>+1 if the huntsman&rsquo;s wisdom is 16+</li>\n<li>+1 if the huntsman&rsquo;s charisma is 16+</li>\n<li>+1 if the huntsman&rsquo;s level is 7+</li>\n<li>+1 if the huntsman has dominated a member of this species before</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Failure indicates the animal is impossible to tame. It may continue attempting to break free.</li>\n<li>Success indicates the animal is subdued; the huntsman must continue to restrain the creature for 1 turn (10 minutes), kneeling on it, commanding it, and forcing submission. Thereafter, it will be docile and relatively obedient.</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 49\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>A defeated animal can be tamed to complete loyalty (ML 12) after 1d4 months of training. It can be trained to attack, fetch, guard, hunt, track, or perform other tasks. Multiple animals can be trained&mdash;even working in flawless synchronization if they are reasonably compatible&mdash;but their total hit dice can never exceed the huntsman&rsquo;s level, and the training time for multiple animals is cumulative.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"huntsman","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.NoxyIedR71kcOuQa"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679254261847,"modifiedTime":1681579182866,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"YVx76WdUAW7WAPXj","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Predator","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 49\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Trained from earliest youth to hunt and kill animals both fleet and robust. The huntsman inflicts +1 hp damage per level of experience when combatting normal and giant-sized animals: amphibians, birds, crustaceans, dinosaurs, fishes, insects, mammals, and reptiles. Does not apply to constructs, d&aelig;mons, elementals, fungi, giants, humanoids, magical beasts, moulds, oozes, otherworldly and alien beings, slimes and jellies, or undead. When used in concert with a successful <em>hide</em> attempt, the initial attack roll is made at a +4 bonus.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"huntsman","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.NoxyIedR71kcOuQa"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679254261847,"modifiedTime":1681579182866,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"YZEGtH9alDuCS8Yv","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Hide","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 49\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>If lightly armoured or unarmoured, able to <em>hide</em> outdoors (wilderness) as a thief of equal level (see <strong>Table 16</strong>), lurking behind bushes, rocks, trees, and the like. Chance-in-twelve reduced by 4 if wearing medium armour; impossible in heavy armour. A huntsman can employ camouflage or remain perfectly still whilst flattened to the ground. Only the slightest movement is permissible (e.g., unsheathing a blade, opening a pouch). Hiding is impossible in direct sunlight, or if the huntsman is observed. In non-wilderness areas (e.g., cities, dungeons), the chance-in-twelve is decreased by 2.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"huntsman","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.NoxyIedR71kcOuQa"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679254261847,"modifiedTime":1681579182865,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"c3oCLrfbkAGXnNLF","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Harvest Venom","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 49\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To extract venom sacs from snakes, spiders, giant insects, and the like, should the opportunity present and appropriate containers be available. Huntsmen learn to dissect venomous creatures. This skill is performed at a base 9-in-12 chance of success. If a <em>12</em> is rolled, a mishap occurs, and the huntsman is exposed (e.g., eyes, nose, skin) to the poisonous fluid. For more information on the extraction of venom, see <strong>Chapter 9: Combat</strong>, <em>poison, venom harvesting</em>.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"huntsman","roll":"d12","rollType":"below","rollTarget":9,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.NoxyIedR71kcOuQa"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679254261847,"modifiedTime":1681579182865,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"cWs1livzha4cQO0W","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Move Silently","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 49\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To stalk like a wolf, moving with preternatural quiet comparable to a thief of equal level (see <strong>Table 16</strong>), if the huntsman is lightly armoured or unarmoured. Chance-in-twelve reduced by 4 if wearing medium armour; impossible in heavy armour. This skill is executed at half the huntsman&rsquo;s normal movement rate.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"huntsman","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.NoxyIedR71kcOuQa"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679254261847,"modifiedTime":1681579182866,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"iCEIDiqe8oRlXS2e","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Track","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 40\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To stalk prey, tracing physical signs and scenting as a predator. A huntsman can <em>track</em> at the below suggested probabilities:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Wilderness:</strong> A base 10-in-12 chance to find, identify, and follow fresh tracks outdoors or in natural caverns.</li>\n<li><strong>Non-Wilderness:</strong> A base 5-in-12 chance to discern tracks in a dungeon, castle, city street, or like setting.</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 50\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Furthermore, the huntsman can identify the tracked animal type (or even exact species) through examination of its spoor, including size, weight, ambulation, rate of movement, etc. N.B.: The referee may alter the chance-in-twelve to <em>track</em> based on prevailing circumstances.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"huntsman","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.T8VdjzWDNBWfyZ8S"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679252841676,"modifiedTime":1681579182866,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"kTL7p6Z9tLOkzu64","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Wilderness Traps","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 50\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To set an outdoor trap, including pits, deadfalls (falling logs/rocks), snares, and spring traps. The huntsman is also adept at finding and removing such traps. These tasks are performed as a thief of equal level performs the <em>manipulate traps</em> skill (see <strong>Table 16</strong>), but the huntsman has no facility with mechanical and/or magical traps.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"huntsman","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.T8VdjzWDNBWfyZ8S"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679252841676,"modifiedTime":1681579182867,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"qfFDagp0vyrQ2usS","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Weapon Mastery","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 50\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p><em>Mastery</em> of one weapon (+1 &ldquo;to hit&rdquo; and +1 damage). The huntsman&rsquo;s first weapon mastery must be an appropriate hunting weapon: axe (hand), bola, boomerang, bow, club (light), crossbow, dagger, dart, hooked throwing knife, javelin, lasso, fighting net, sling, spear (short or long), trident (long), or whip. Additional weapons may be mastered at 4th, 8th, and 12th levels, though these may be any weapons. As noted in <strong>Chapter 6: Equipment</strong>, the attack rate for melee weapons and the rates of fire for most missile weapons improve through weapon mastery. For more information on weapon mastery, see <strong>Chapter 9: Combat</strong>, <em>weapon skill</em>.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"huntsman","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.K1OLRl8YTN53zIp4"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679250294860,"modifiedTime":1681579182866,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"wOkluIscmYhaawb8","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Alertness","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 39\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Reduces by one (&minus;1) on a d6 roll the party&rsquo;s chance to be <em>surprized</em>.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"huntsman","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679254261847,"modifiedTime":1681579182865,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"yRGV3zTPFXvKfcla","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Melee Expert","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 28\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 41\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>At 7th level, a huntsman&rsquo;s standard <em>melee</em> attack rate improves from 1/1 to 3/2. Note that <em>weapon mastery</em> can further increase attack rate.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"huntsman 7","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.UbQiMVdAegqnmdRv"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679250510524,"modifiedTime":1681579182865,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"zyEXWNNCed1mmWjY","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
